poxchat for Debian
==================

Relationship to hexchat
-----------------------

PoxChat is a GTK4 fork of HexChat. The two packages are installable
side-by-side: PoxChat ships its own binary (`/usr/bin/poxchat`),
configuration directory (`~/.config/poxchat`) and AppStream identity
(`io.github.evilnet.PoxChat`).

Scripting plugins
-----------------

The Perl, Python and Lua scripting plugins are shipped as separate
binary packages so that users who only want the IRC client are not
forced to pull in language runtimes:

  * `poxchat-perl`    - Perl scripting
  * `poxchat-python`  - Python 3 scripting
  * `poxchat-lua`     - Lua (LuaJIT) scripting

Drop scripts into `~/.config/poxchat/addons/`.

FiSH encryption
---------------

The FiSH plugin (Blowfish channel encryption with DH1080 key exchange)
is provided by `poxchat-plugin-fishlim`. FiSH is a legacy protocol with
known weaknesses; treat it as an obfuscation layer rather than a
modern end-to-end encrypted messenger.

